@node CONFIG "The MIDAS.dat-file"
How to make MIDAS my own slave
@{b}______________________________@{ub}

The  idea  of  MIDAS  is  that  you  type  in the
question while MIDAS prints an introduction.  You
are  able  to  edit  these  texts.   And its also
possible to edit the errors which appear when you
type in an "<" in your answer.  Just feel free to
grab  your  favourite text- editor, e.g CygnusED,
and  load the MIDAS.dat-file, that needs to be in
the  same  directory as MIDAS.  At first you will
find  three  introductions  and  after  a CR-line
three errors.  You can edit this file as often as
you want it.  But keep the following rules:

 Please answer me this Question:  \
 What about this , MIDAS:          > Introductions
 Can you please response this:    /
                                  > free CR-Line
 No way today!                    \
 More precise, please!             > Errors
 Unable to find match             /
                                  > End of file

Dont for get to end every line with the Returnkey
directly after the text.
@endnode
